title: More Growth, Consolidation, And M&A Expected For Hemp Industry In 2019
text: By William Sumner, Hemp Business Journal Contributor From acquisitions to equity investments, the North American hemp industry has been awash in capital investment since the Farm Bill 2018 was federally passed in the United States last December.

title: Dow, S&P 500 rally despite bad market breadth
text: The rallies in the Dow Jones Industrial Average DJIA, +0.37% and the S&P 500 SPX, +0.09% come despite internal market readings that suggest the overall stock market is actually declining.

title: Rate Cut Coming: Is "Data Dependent" Out the Window?
text: Is an inevitable rate cut impervious to a continued narrative of relatively strong economic data?

title: After Hitting 3000 For First Time, Market Mulls Delta Results, More Powell
text: The S&P 500 Index (SPX) hit 3000 for the first time Wednesday on dovish testimony from Fed Chair Jerome Powell, but is there meaning in this big new round number?

title: Venture giant Andreessen Horowitz doubles down on fintech with newest hire from Credit Karma
text: Andreessen Horowitz is hiring Credit Karma's Anish Acharya as its newest general partner.

title: Market Sprints A "3K": New All-Time High Above 3000 As Rate Cut Seen
text: More Powell testimony is on tap today, but it seems unlikely he’d make too many new headlines after his dovish view pushed stocks to new all-time highs yesterday.

title: Stock edge up at open Thursday in wake of Fed's Powell on Wednesday signaling lower interest rates likely
text:
Stocks opened higher Thursday, building on gains that saw the Nasdaq Composite index end in record territory Wednesday, and the SP500 hit 3,000 for the first time intraday, after Federal Reserve Chairman Jerome Powell reinforced expectations for an interest rate cut later this month.
The Dow  was up 0.6 % at 26,942 while the SP500  rose 0.2% to 2,998 and Nasdaq  was up 0.1% at 8,213.

title: U.S. underlying inflation firming; labor market tightening
text: U.S. underlying consumer prices increased by the most in nearly 1-1/2 years in June amid solid gains in the costs of a range of goods and services, but that will likely not change expectations the Federal Reserve will cut interest rates this month.

title: 4 Funds to Buy From Sectors That Added Most Jobs in June
text: New job additions in June were broad-based despite fears of slowing economic growth.

title: Cargill adjusted profit slides 41% on trade tensions, U.S. floods
text: Commodities trader Cargill Inc [CARG.UL] reported a 41% slump in adjusted quarterly profit on Thursday, as the U.S.-China trade war led to supply disruptions and flooding in the central United States hit marketing and transportation of grains.

title: Futures pare gains after inflation data
text: U.S. stock index futures pared gains on Thursday after U.S. underlying consumer prices increased by the most in nearly 1-1/2 years in June, dimming hopes for an aggressive interest cut by the Federal Reserve this month.

title: Healthcare Stocks Lead Futures Higher; Delta Stock Gets 737 Max Boost
text: Walgreens led the Dow Jones and Nasdaq 100, Cigna topped the S&P 500 early Thursday as healthcare stocks rallied on President Trump's kidney initiative.

title: World Gold Council: Federal Reserve, Central Bank Rate Cuts To Drive Gold Investment In H2
text: The WGC is the latest institution to predict strong conditions for gold in the second half of 2019. Is the safe-haven set to hit fresh price peaks in the weeks and months ahead?

title: Foxconn's Wisconsin plant won't bring as many jobs as it promised
text: It'll reportedly employee 1,500 people when it opens next May.

title: OPEC sees lower 2020 demand for its oil, points to surplus
text: OPEC on Thursday forecast world demand for its crude will decline next year as rivals pump more, pointing to the return of a surplus despite an OPEC-led pact to restrain supplies.

title: Fed's Powell Reaffirms a Rate Cut: Winners & Losers
text: Powell says trade uncertainties and worries about global growth continue to weigh on the U.S. economy, which is likely to lead the central bank to lower rates soon.

title: Wall Street banks bailing on troubled U.S. farm sector
text: In the wake of the U.S. housing meltdown of the late 2000s, JPMorgan Chase & Co hunted for new ways to expand its loan business beyond the troubled mortgage sector.

title: Bleak China autos outlook triggers raft of profit warnings
text: Auto suppliers Johnson Electric Holdings  and Sensirion  slashed their earnings forecasts on Thursday, blaming a slowdown in car sales and pessimism about the prospects of a Chinese car sector recovery.

title: Vitol faces possible $6 million fine for U.S. power market manipulation
text: Global energy trader Vitol faces a possible fine of $6 million from a U.S. energy regulator for alleged manipulation in California's power market, an order from the regulator showed.

title: Stocks, Treasuries Rise As Rate-Cut Bets Mount: Markets Wrap
text: European equities climbed alongside U.S. futures and Asian stocks as investors cheered fresh signs from central bankers that rates are headed lower.

title: Risk Factors Feeding Hedge Fund Performance
text: There is presently a significant spike in risk factor correlations above the historic highs of 2007/2008. Not surprisingly, correlation among hedge fund returns are also near multi-year highs as the current environment spawns “risk on/risk off” market action.

title: Norwegian Air CEO steps down, sees 737 MAX flying in Oct
text: Norwegian Air's Bjoern Kjos stepped down on Thursday as chief executive of the budget airline he co-founded.

title: IPO mania produced record exits for VCs in second quarter, PitchBook says
text: Uber accounted for almost half of the exit value from venture-backed companies in Q2, while Slack, Zoom, Pinterest and CrowdStrike made up most of the rest.

title: Oil hits six-week high as storm builds in Gulf of Mexico
text: Oil futures hit a six-week high on Thursday as a storm built in the Gulf of Mexico, threatening crude output, while an incident with a British tanker in the Middle East highlighted ongoing tensions in the region.
